✅ 1️⃣ Lucide React install
npm install lucide-react
2️⃣ Import and use icons in your React component
import { Home, User } from "lucide-react";
export default function App() {
  return (
    <div className="flex gap-4">
      <Home size={24} color="blue" />
      <User size={24} color="green" />
    </div>
  );
}
3️⃣ Optional: Using with Tailwind CSS

If you use Tailwind, you can style icons like any other element:

<Home className="w-6 h-6 text-red-500" />

Lucide React, here’s a list of popular and useful icons you might need for different UI purposes:

1️⃣ Navigation / Layout

Home – Homepage

Menu – Hamburger menu

ChevronLeft / ChevronRight – Pagination / sliders

ArrowLeft / ArrowRight – Back/forward navigation

Grid – Dashboard view

List – List view

2️⃣ User / Profile

User – Profile

Users – Multiple users / team

UserPlus – Add user

UserCheck – Verified user

LogIn / LogOut – Authentication

3️⃣ Actions

Edit – Edit / update

Trash – Delete

Plus – Add / create

Check – Success / confirmation

X – Close / cancel

RefreshCw – Refresh / reload

4️⃣ Communication / Feedback

MessageCircle – Chat / comments

Mail – Email

Bell – Notification

AlertCircle – Error / warning

Info – Info message

CheckCircle – Success notification

5️⃣ Media / Files

Camera – Photos / camera

Image – Image placeholder

File – Document / file

Folder – Folder

Download / Upload – File actions

Video – Video content

6️⃣ E-commerce / Payment

ShoppingCart – Cart

CreditCard – Payment

Tag – Product tag / discount

DollarSign – Pricing

Heart – Wishlist / favorites
